creating user :-
$ usermod bharath
$ passwd bharath
switching to the user :-
$ sudo -su bharath
u will get error like this bharath  is not in the sudoers file. This incident will be reported.so will do like this
then switch to root first need to modify sudoers file
$ sudo su -
$ sudo nano /etc/sudoers
bharath ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL
then exit from root:-
switch to user :-
$ sudo -su bharath
$ sudo su -
done..............
  
